      "weather": "Fine",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAURIE'S FERRARI (1) was well supported last time and rocketed out of the boxes with a strong early sectional, going on to clock 22.88 in a neck win at The Gardens over 400m. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. TOMMY'S DAWN (5) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 7 lengths at Richmond in a handy 22.69 beating Terrell Banner. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Sure to be thereabouts. I'M ALRIGHT (2) doesn't have the best strike-rate. Finished in the minors latest when third (22.98) at The Gardens and may be close to breaking through. Form at the trip sound including four wins. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Bold showing expected. REBORN SPARK (8) was in the money two back in a Grade 5 at Richmond then jumped from a squeeze draw last time and was not far away when second (18.22) over 320m at Richmond. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide.",
